<p class="style2">General Application Questions::</p>
<ul>
  <li>How do I add a Task?<a name="AddTask" id="AddTask"></a>
    <span class="style3">download instructions</span>
    <ul>
      <li>From the Task Calendar
        <ul>
          <li>Click on a day in the Task Calendar (select the day you would like to have that date auto fill in the form)</li>
          <li>Enter the required information
            <ul>
              <li>Select the Task Type </li>
              <li>Confirm the correct date</li>
              <li>Enter the Scheduled Start Time (click in the field and a calendar selector will appear)</li>
              <li>Select the Field</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Enter any additional information about the Task
            <ul>
              <li>To enter an Employee, click in the Employee field and you will see the appropriate list (this is a multi-select field)</li>
              <li>To enter Equipment to be used, click in the Employee field and you will see the appropriate list  (this is a multi-select field)</li>
              <li>Select a Product. This list will only be populated with Products that are currently in your Inventory. If you do not see it in the list, please verify the correct Inventory has been added.</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>**Additional Information: Once you check the Completed option and save the Task, you will not be able to edit the Task again. If the task was tied to an Inventory item, the Quantity Used will then be subtracted from the Product's Inventory total.</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>What is a AddUpdate User?<a name="FacilitiesUser" id="FacilitiesUser"></a> </li>
</ul>
<ul>
  <ul>
    <li>A AddUpdate User has restricted access to the system and can only update and view the Events Calendar. If a AddUpdate User also needs access to the full system, you will need to add the role of Employee on the Employee list page.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <li>How often is the weather updated?<a name="WeatherUpdates" id="WeatherUpdates"></a> </li>
</ul>
<ul>
  <ul>
    <li>The weather is updated daily for the previous day's data. The information is being pulled based on the zip code of the organization. If you would like to use a different zip code for this information, please get with your Account Manager.</li>
  </ul>
</ul>
