<p class="style2">Admin Questions::</p>
<ul>
  <li>How do I add a Product?<a name="AddProduct" id="AddProduct"></a>
    <span class="style3">download instructions</span>
    <ul>
      <li>From  the main navigation, select Admin Tools</li>
      <li>Select Products</li>
      <li>Select the proper category: Materials, Fertilizers,  or Chemicals</li>
      <li>Select the &quot;+&quot; icon on the top left of the grid</li>
      <li>Enter the Name</li>
      <li>Enter the Description (optional)</li>
      <li>Click Save</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <blockquote>
    <p>**Additional Information: Adding a Product will make it available for selection while creating a Purchase Order, it will not be an option when creating a Task until you add it to Inventory.</p>
  </blockquote>
  <li>How do I create a PO?<a name="CreatePO" id="CreatePO"></a>
      <span class="style3">download instructions</span>
      <ul>
          <li>From  the main navigation, select Admin Tools</li>
          <li>Select Purchase Orders</li>
         <li>Select Current </li>
          <li>Select the &quot;+&quot; icon on the top left of the grid</li>
          <li>From the Vendor drop down, select the Vendor</li>
          <li>Click on the &quot;+&quot; icon next to the Product(s) you wish to order</li>
          <li>When you have selected all the Products for this order, go to the List Items grid at the bottom of the page. The Products you selected will be listed here.</li>
          <li>Click on each Product to enter:
            <ul>
              <li>Quantity Ordered</li>
              <li>Unit Type - if the Unit Type you need is not an option, an Admin will need to enter it on the Enumerations page found under Admin Tools.</li>
              <li>Size of Unit and Price are optional.</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Click  Save</li>
          <li>Once you have entered this information for all Products, click Commit on the bottom left of the page.</li>
          <li>Your PO has been Committed and will now appear in the Current Purchase Orders list.
              <p>**Additional Information: You must have Admin rights to see the Admin Tools option in the main navigation</p>
          </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>How do I add Inventory?<a name="AddInventory" id="AddInventory"></a>  <span class="style3">download instructions</span></li>
  <ul>
    <li>      From  the main navigation, select Admin Tools</li>
    <li>Select Purchase Orders</li>
    <li>Select Current </li>
    <li>Click on the Commit icon (&quot;C&quot;) of the Purchase Order you would like to receive
      <ul>
        <li>The Commit icon is located on the right of the grid</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Click on each Product you would like to receive</li>
    <li>Enter the Quantity Received    </li>
    <li>Click the Completed box</li>
    <li>Click Save    </li>
    <li>When you have completed this process for each Product, you will no longer see any Products listed on the Purchase Order.  Click on the &quot;Close This Purchase Order&quot; button.    </li>
    <li>Select
        Admin Tools, then Inventory to verify the Quantity Received has been added to your Inventory
      <p>**Additional Information: You must have Admin rights to see the Admin Tools option in the main navigation.</p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</ul>
